description: Middle Eastern Music Meets Jazz Improvisation. The name Asef has its origins in Arabic and Persian cultures. The members of the group bring to the stage many years of experience playing a variety of music from around the world including Balkan folk, Tango, Klezmer, Flamenco and Bebop. Their compositions embrace this vast range of musical sounds taking the audience on a truly unique musical journey.

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. description: Looking for fresh outfits to wear dancing? Let's raid each others' giveaway piles this Sunday during the SwingSoul party! This swap is intended for womens' clothes only. Here's how it works: 1. Put aside a pile of (clean) clothes that no longer bring you joy, BUT ARE DANCEABLE. 2. Bring your bag of DANCEABLE contributions with you when you come to SwingSoul on Sunday. Leave it with us to sort in the studio lobby, ideally before 8pm or shortly after. 3. Swap will start at 8pm (after the classes end) 4. Then you can browse around, try things on, and take whatever inspires you! Suggestions: T-shirts, blouses, tanks, sweaters, jeans, leggings, slacks, dance shoes clothes for dancing WCS! Don't bring this time: street shoes, coats, dresses, skirts, jewellery, men's clothing. (Maybe at a later date) We hope you join us for this opportunity to refresh your Westie wardrobe!

description: Foundation Class (6:30–7:35 PM) Perfect for absolute beginners or dancers looking to strengthen their foundation! In this class, we’ll break down the essential steps, body movement, and partner connection in a fun environment. You’ll learn the basics with proper technique while also adding styling to make your dancing look and feel smooth on the dance floor. No experience or partner needed—just bring your curiosity and energy! Intermediate Class (7:35–8:40 PM) Ready to level up? This class is designed for dancers who already feel comfortable with the basics and want to challenge themselves. We’ll dive into more fun patterns while also exploring musicality—how to connect those movements to the music in a more expressive way. Get ready to build confidence, fluidity, and your own unique style!
location: 111 Superior St, Victoria, BC V8V 1T2, Canada

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Swingouts are the iconic move in the Lindy Hop repertoire! This move is easy to do, but hard to do well. In this series we will examine the technique required to make the Swingout feel amazing and look fantastic, plus variations to add a little more spice! This is a five week lesson series for advanced beginner and intermediate dancers. Those that are comfortable with six and eight count basic moves and the principles of leading and following are welcome to join us. Our class emphasizes learning in a safe, friendly and supportive environment. You do not need to sign up with a partner. Registration includes entry to our monthly social dance, Jazz Cats Social. Instructors: Barney Lee & Katie Tang. Classes will start at 8:30pm and run until 9:40pm - please arrive by 8:20pm on the first evening to check in and sign your waiver.
source: Strictly Lindy Hop Swing Vancouver, BC
location: New Westminster Secondary School - dance studio, 820 6th St, New Westminster, BC V3M 3S9, Canada

Free admission if you've never danced before. No one turned away for lack of funds. Bring your own water bottle. Be considerate of others’ decision to mask or not, and be prepared to put on a mask as a courtesy to your dance partner if they request it.

Every Monday | June–August 5:30–7:30 PM 1.5-hour dance class followed by a 30-minute outdoor social. Dance style rotates monthly — check our content calendar on our website for full details! This free outdoor event is open to everyone — no partner or dance experience needed. All ages, bodies, and abilities are warmly welcomed! description:
Rehearsal for our Student Bachata Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha- Beginner Intermediate
dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Swingouts are the iconic move in the Lindy Hop repertoire! This move is easy to do, but hard to do well. In this series we will examine the technique required to make the Swingout feel amazing and look fantastic, plus variations to add a little more spice! This is a five week lesson series for advanced beginner and intermediate dancers. Those that are comfortable with six and eight count basic moves and the principles of leading and following are welcome to join us. Our class emphasizes learning in a safe, friendly and supportive environment. You do not need to sign up with a partner. Registration includes entry to our monthly social dance, Jazz Cats Social. Instructors: Barney Lee & Katie Tang. Classes will start at 8:30pm and run until 9:40pm - please arrive by 8:20pm on the first evening to check in and sign your waiver.
source: Strictly Lindy Hop Swing Vancouver, BC
location: New Westminster Secondary School - dance studio, 820 6th St, New Westminster, BC V3M 3S9, Canada

description: Blues and Lindy Dance featuring all the usual suspects and special guests. Nothing else like it. Slow Drag and Traditional Blues and Swing Dance 7-10 dance featuring a line up of the Swing Out Super Stars~!!! All styles of dance and partner dance are welcome. Also you do not have to dance to come out; this Speakeasy is a great place to enjoy something from the bar and enjoy the cabaret. This month only From 6-7 there is a FREE HOUR LONG DROP IN Lindy Lesson available for FREE for anyone with a ticket to the dance!! The venue can be hard to find - It's in the Artiste Building at 2050 Scotia Street, but you must enter through the glass door by the loading bay at the back of the building. See the pin on our website for the location, and don't give up you will find it! The Swing Out is a safe and welcoming space for people from all backgrounds including the BIPOC and 2SLGBTQIA+ communities. Consent is always a must on the dancefloor. We respectfully acknowledge that this event is held on the unceded homelands of the xʷməθkʷəy̓əm (Musqueam), Skwxwú7mesh (Squamish), and səl̓ílwətaʔɬ (Tsleil-Waututh) First Nations.
location: The Dusty Flowerpot Cabaret, 2050 Scotia Street, Vancouver, BC V5T 4T1
